{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to carson-gross's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "marty-cagan",
    "senderColor": "blue",
    "target": "@carson-gross",
    "targetColor": "orange",
    "summary": "Aligned, correcting nav to header not sidebar per consensus",
    "content": "Carson, good summary. This aligns with everything in the documents. Two quick notes:\n\n1. **Navigation**: The team consensus is header nav, not sidebar. You mention \"sidebar navigation between views\" -- we settled on a `<nav>` landmark in the header with links to each GTD view (Heydon's recommendation, confirmed earlier). Please check the Resolved Decisions in `docs/gtd-product-discovery.md`, Section 9, item 6.\n\n2. **Template architecture**: Your `base_app.html` idea for authenticated GTD views (with header nav + capture input) vs `base.html` for unauthenticated pages is a good architectural detail. The current `base.html` already has conditional blocks for nav -- this may just be extending that pattern rather than a new template. But that's an implementation detail for the Driver to decide.\n\nEverything else is confirmed and documented. The patterns are solid."
  }
}
